  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Trim the woody ends off your <strong>asparagus</strong>,<strong> </strong>then chop them in half</p><p>Tip: Alternatively, bend the woody ends of the asparagus until they snap!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-linguine/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for an initial 7 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-linguine/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-linguine/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Roll your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-linguine/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta has been cooking for 7 min, add the<strong> halved</strong> <strong>asparagus</strong> and <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until just tender</p><p>Once tender, drain and return to the pot, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-linguine/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pot to a medium heat, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span><strong> butter</strong> and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, then give everything a good mix up until the butter has melted</p><p>Squeeze in the juice of <strong>half</strong> the<strong> lemon[s] </strong>and add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped basil </strong>with<strong> half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Add a splash of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-linguine/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>bacon lardons</strong> to the pot, give everything another good mix and cook for 1 min further or until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta â€“ this is your <strong>crispy bacon & lemony asparagus linguine</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad,</strong> then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-bacon-and-lemony-asparagus-linguine/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy bacon & lemony asparagus linguine</strong> with the <strong>salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>salad</strong> with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and<strong> remaining chopped basil</strong></p><p>Garnish with a<strong> lemon</strong> <strong>wedge </strong>and season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
